---
description: Right-click / long-press context menus for all dashboard entity data
alwaysApply: true
---

# Dashboard Entity Context Menus

Every interactive data row or list item in the Ampere Studio dashboard (Stripe, Square, CMS, and future surfaces) MUST support a right-click context menu on desktop and long-press on mobile with the same actions as the row's 3-dot menu when one exists.

## Required pattern

1. Prefer shared wrappers from `components/cms/entity-row-actions.tsx`:
   - `EntityRowActions` for table/list rows that also show a 3-dot dropdown
   - `EntityContextMenu` for overview/chart/list chips that are context-menu-only
2. Keep entity-specific actions in per-entity modules that render the same items into both menus:
   - Stripe orders: `components/cms/stripe/orders/order-actions.tsx`
   - Stripe products: `components/cms/stripe/product-actions.tsx`
   - Square orders: `components/cms/square/order-actions.tsx`
   - Square products: `components/cms/square/product-actions.tsx`
3. Add `entityContextTargetClass` on the clickable/long-press target so mobile does not show the native callout.
4. Nested entities (e.g. products inside an order) get their own product menu. Stop context-menu bubbling so the parent order menu does not steal the event.
5. Overview / analytics rows (recent orders, failed payments, top products) must use the same entity menus as the dedicated list pages. Do not ship view-only links without the context menu.

## When adding a new entity surface

- If the UI shows an order, product, submission, or similar record, wrap it with the matching entity context menu before merge.
- Actions must match what that entity supports today (View / Edit / Archive / Delete / etc.). Do not invent Square order refunds, etc., unless the API exists.
- For Square line items, resolve `catalog_object_id` (variation) to the parent ITEM via `buildVariationProductIndex` before linking to `/products/[id]`.

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// BAD: row with only a link / 3-dot dropdown and no right-click menu
<TableRow>
  <TableCell><Link href={`/orders/${id}`}>...</Link></TableCell>
  <TableCell><DropdownMenu>...</DropdownMenu></TableCell>
</TableRow>

// GOOD: shared dual menu
<OrderRowActions order={order}>
  {(dropdown) => (
    <TableRow className={entityContextTargetClass}>
      ...
      <TableCell>{dropdown}</TableCell>
    </TableRow>
  )}
</OrderRowActions>
```
